## Purpose

Describe the kind of renderer experience this template should guide. Do not
copy product copy, campaign language, or user data from the source.

## Safety Boundary

- Display guidance only; never execute source code from the referenced design.
- Do not copy backend targets, providers, policies, permissions, secrets, true
  action ids, true button labels, source asset references, fonts, visual
  identity assets, or executable implementation files.
- Abstract placeholders are allowed when they cannot operate.
- Every real interaction must map back to a verified operable W3A contract and
  pass through `w3a-core`.

## Layout Profile

```json
{
  "layout_id": "<family.name.layout>",
  "viewport": {
    "desktop_min_width": 1024,
    "mobile_behavior": "<stack, drawer, tabs, or other non-operable layout rule>"
  },
  "regions": [
    {
      "id": "<abstract_region_id>",
      "role": "<abstract_region_role>",
      "content": ["<abstract_component_role>"]
    }
  ],
  "grid": {
    "columns": "<abstract column structure>",
    "gap": 16
  }
}
```

## Visual Tokens

```json
{
  "font_stack": ["system-ui", "sans-serif"],
  "density": "comfortable",
  "radius": {
    "panel": 8,
    "card": 8,
    "control": 6
  },
  "colors": {
    "background": "#000000",
    "surface": "#111111",
    "text": "#ffffff",
    "accent": "#7cc4ff"
  },
  "effects": {
    "motion": "optional and disabled under reduced motion"
  }
}
```

## Component Roles

```json
{
  "abstract_button_role": {
    "shape": "describe geometry, spacing, icon/text balance, and wrapping",
    "states": ["default", "hover", "focus", "disabled"],
    "notes": "describe role and shape only; do not name concrete actions"
  },
  "abstract_panel_role": {
    "shape": "describe panel structure and density",
    "behavior": "visual behavior only; no provider calls or target semantics"
  },
  "action_role_slots": {
    "primary_submit": {
      "match": "verified W3A action that writes/submits or starts the main user-confirmed flow",
      "component": "<abstract_button_role>",
      "fallback": "derive a same-style primary control if this exact role is missing; do not create a feature"
    },
    "secondary_action": {
      "match": "verified cancel, close, back, or low-risk secondary action",
      "component": "<abstract_button_role>"
    },
    "compact_icon_action": {
      "match": "verified row, card, toolbar, or repeated control that should stay compact",
      "component": "<abstract_button_role>",
      "notes": "icon or short-label treatment only; the UI plan still binds the verified W3A action"
    },
    "destructive_confirm": {
      "match": "verified destructive or irreversible action that already requires confirmation",
      "component": "<abstract_button_role>",
      "notes": "visual danger treatment only; W3A confirmation still comes from w3a-core"
    },
    "navigation_or_filter": {
      "match": "display navigation, search, filter, or tab control",
      "component": "<abstract_button_role>",
      "notes": "display-only unless bound to a verified W3A action in the UI plan"
    }
  }
}
```

## W3A Block Mapping

```json
{
  "ㄆㄤ": "map to an abstract message/list surface; bind only to verified action placeholders at render time",
  "ㄗㄞ": "map to abstract list rows or cards",
  "ㄔㄠ": "map to an abstract form/composer surface",
  "ㄙㄞ": "map to an abstract search or filter affordance",
  "ㄉㄟ": "map to an abstract detail/context surface",
  "ㄇㄢ": "map to safe plain text"
}
```

## Interaction Guidance

- Prefer stable dimensions for repeated controls and status elements.
- Keep focus states visible without implying trust or permission state.
- Keep mutating-operation confirmation visible when the verified W3A contract
  requires it.
- Use placeholders such as `<declared_action_slot>` only for abstract mapping.
- Every rendered button must either bind to a verified W3A action in the UI plan
  or be marked display-navigation/display-only. If the template lacks a matching
  role, derive a fallback from the template's tokens and record it as styling,
  not as a new feature.

